"provide a search and sort based interface for locating books that is *much* "
"more efficient than any possible folder scheme you could come up with for "
"your collection. Indeed, once you become comfortable using calibre's "
"interface to find, sort and browse your collection, you won't ever feel the "
"need to hunt through the files on your disk to find a book again. By "
"managing books in its own folder structure of Author -> Title -> Book files,"
" calibre is able to achieve a high level of reliability and standardization."
" To illustrate why a search/tagging based interface is superior to folders, "
"consider the following. Suppose your book collection is nicely sorted into "
"folders with the following scheme::"
